Cell.Text: The rebels have agreed to cease hostilities until we hash out this treaty. Suffice it to say I'm not holding my breath.
For the moment we have ceased hostilities. We'll see what these Imperials have to say. I doubt we'll come to any lasting agreement.
Things are quiet for the moment. That won't last long. As soon as a new campaign starts, I want you there. Stay close. See me tomorrow.
The gods have granted us peace for the moment. But that won't last long. I'm sure trouble will be stirred up soon enough.
<<Shared>> It's good we hold the Reach. Were the rebels to gain control, the silver mines would give them coin to hire more thugs and expand their violence.
<<Shared>> We need to stem the flow of silver to the rebellion. Until we retake the Reach, the Stormcloaks will plunder it's mines to fund further violence.
<<Shared>> Hjaalmarch is an important buffer zone between the rebel forces and the capital. Ulfric will try to break through at some point.
<<Shared>> I'm losing my patience with this damn war. We must take Hjaalmarch back! The Stormcloaks will be beating upon the doors of the capital soon.
<<Shared>> Ulfric will want to take Whiterun from us. But we will hold fast. We can't give the rebellion free reign through the center of Skyrim.
<<Shared>> I can't believe we lost Whiterun. The rebels have a great advantage in controlling the center now. We must take it back!
<<Shared>> By holding onto Falkreath, we control access to the Reach, Whiterun, and the Rift. Ulfric will likely try for it soon. We'll be there to stop him.
<<Shared>> I fear losing Falkreath may give too much advantage to Ulfric. The rebels now control access to the Reach, Whiterun, and the Rift. I want it back.
<<Shared>> Taking the Pale gives us another port in Dawnstar, and puts us within striking distance of Windhelm. That should make Ulfric a bit more cautious, eh?
<<Shared>> Controlling the Pale gives Ulfric a port town and takes the pressure off of Windhelm. But it's only a matter of time before it's back in our hands.
<<Shared>> Now that we have Winterhold, I can garrison some troops there until I'm ready to march on Windhelm.
<<Shared>> There's not much up there, but if we can regain Winterhold, our proximity to Windhelm should keep Ulfric wary and wasting troops garrisoned at home.
<<Shared>> I almost can't believe it's over. The rebellion is squashed, Windhelm is free. I must admit, Ulfric put up a stronger fight than I was expecting.
<<Shared>> We will oust Ulfric from Windhelm soon enough. And when we do, I'll have his head on a plate.
<<Shared>> Taking control of the Rift was a great victory. Ulfric must be rather nervous with us so close to his door step.
<<Shared>> We need the Rift. We need to regain control of it before we can march on Windhelm without worry about our rear guard.
<<Shared>> I almost can't believe it. The Empire has been defeated. The world bears witness to the power and righteousness of the sons and daughters of Skyrim.
<<Shared>> Soon enough we will march on Solitude. And on that day the heroes of Sovngarde will march with us, and the Empire will fall to it's knees in fear.
<<Shared>> Now that the Empire has been driven from the Reach we can put a stop to the raping of her silver mines. That silver belongs in Skyrim.
<<Shared>> The Empire's ravenous hunger for Skyrim's silver makes them fierce. But rest assured, we'll win the Reach and wrest it from their greedy paws.
<<Shared>> Tullius must be getting nervous. Taking Hjaalmarch we're practically in his back yard now. As soon as we're able, we'll march on Solitude.
<<Shared>> We should take Hjaalmarch. It'll be an important pressure point on the Imperials. We'd be within spitting distance of the capital.
<<Shared>> We've driven the Imperials out of Whiterun. This is good. Very good. We now control the center. It's a powerful position. One I aim to keep.
<<Shared>> The Imperials have really dug into Whiterun. We'll wrest it from them soon enough. We must. It's central position is key.
<<Shared>> I'm proud we liberated Falkreath from the Empire. In many ways it's the heart and soul of Skyrim. Not to mention it's rather strategic position.
<<Shared>> The Empire thinks it holds Falkreath from us. But the souls of Skyrim's bravest are buried there and will fill our hearts and strengthen our blades.
<<Shared>> Tullius has camps in the Pale, entertaining thoughts of battle. The Empire still underestimates the force of our cause. It will be their undoing.
<<Shared>> I can't believe we let them take the Pale. Losing the port of Dawnstar is lessened only by the threat of imperial forces being so close to Windhelm.
<<Shared>> I'm not sure why Tullius is wasting his time trying to take Winterhold from us. But if he wants to throw his men away, I'll gladly accept that gift.
<<Shared>> I don't like Imperial troops holed up in Winterhold such a close march to Windhelm. So I'm sending a campaign up there to take it back.
<<Shared>> Damn Tullius. He's pocketed men in the Rift. It's dangerous having Imperials skulking about on the southern border of Eastmarch.
<<Shared>> Losing the Rift gives Tullius easy access to the south of Eastmarch. Talos preserve us. We must take it back!
[S] Here's your pay. It's never enough for what we do, but war gives us warriors it's own kind of benefits, doesn't it?
Are you sure? It's rightfully yours, but this money could go to getting better weapons and armor, and making repairs to the settlements we control.

Node.Caption: CWSalaryTopic: I'd like to collect my salary.

Cell.Text: [S] Here you go. Your continued assistance to the cause is appreciated.
[S] I wish more had the dedication and strength of character that you demonstrate. I'll be sure this gets put to good use.

Node.Caption: CWSalaryNo: I'll donate my salary to the cause.
